Kollsnes is a natural gas processing plant operated by Statoil on the southern part of the island Oøy in the municipality of Øygarden in Hordaland county, Norway. It processes the natural gas from the Troll, Kvitebjørn, and Visund gas fields. Kollsnes has a capacity of 143,000,000 cubic metres (3.8×1010 US gal) of natural gas per day.
